<subpara1><title>Hazardous Materials Icons</title><para>Icons are
used in this manual to identify dangers associated with hazardous
materials. The icons used and their definitions are as follows:<tabmat
frame="none" colsep="0"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1"
colwidth="1.5in"><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="3.5in"><tbody>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="bio" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1" icon="yes">
</graphic></entry>
<entry>BIOLOGICAL: The abstract symbol bug shows that a material may
contain bacteria or viruses that present a danger to life or health.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="chemical" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1"
icon="yes"></graphic></entry>
<entry>CHEMICAL: The symbol of drops of liquid onto a hand shows that
the material will cause burns or irritation of skin and tissues.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="explode" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1"
icon="yes"></graphic></entry>
<entry>EXPLOSION: The rapidly expanding symbol shows that the material
may explode if subjected to high temperatures, sources of ignition
or high pressure.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="goggles" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1"
icon="yes"></graphic></entry>
<entry>EYE PROTECTION: The symbol of a person wearing goggles shows
that the material will injure eyes.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="fire" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1" icon="yes">
</graphic></entry>
<entry>FIRE: The symbol of a flame shows that the material can ignite
and burn.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="poison" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1"
icon="yes"></graphic></entry>
<entry>POISON: The symbol of a skull and crossbones shows that the
material is poisonous or a danger to life.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="rada" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1" icon="yes">
</graphic></entry>
<entry>RADIATION: The symbol of three circular wedges shows that radioactive
energy is emitted which can injure tissue and organs.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><graphic boardno="vapor" reprowid="0.4in" scalefit="1" icon="yes">
</graphic></entry>
<entry>VAPOR: The symbol of a human figure in a cloud shows that the
material gives off vapors that are a danger to life or health.</entry>
</row>
</tbody></tgroup></tabmat></para>
</subpara1>
</para0>
