<para0 hcp="1" verstatus="ver"><title>Use of "Shall", "Will", "Should",
and "May"</title>
<para>The word "shall" is used to express a provision that is binding.
 The words "should" and "may" are used when it is necessary to express
non-mandatory provisions.  The word "will" may be used to express
a mandatory declaration of purpose or when it is necessary to express
a future event.</para>
</para0>
