<symsect rtermwidth="6.5in" ltermwidth="1.0in" verstatus="ver"><title>Symbol
Definition</title>
<para>The following list of symbols are used in this manual and adhere
to requirements of DoD specification MIL-STD-38784.</para>
<symtitle>List of Symbols</symtitle>
<term><esds></term><def><applicabil applicref="a"></applicabil> This
is the symbol used to indicate Electrostatic Discharge Sensitive parts.
ESDS parts require to be handled in accordance with the ESDS device
handling procedures in TO 00-25-234.  This explanation shall be preceded
by a CAUTION heading.</def>
<term>**HCI**</term><def>This is the symbol used for a Harness Critical
Item. This shall include an explanation that the HCI symbol establishes
special requirements limiting changes and substitutions, and that
the specific parts listed must be used to ensure hardness is not degraded.
 This statement shall be preceded by a CAUTION heading.</def>
</symsect>
</foreword>
<purpose applicref="a"><title> Purpose</title>
<para>This manual contains a series of Work Packages (WP) and Subordinate
Work Packages (SWP) providing system level procedures for organizational/intermediate/depot
level maintenance and troubleshooting of the support equipment for
the XXXX system.<seqlist>
<title>This is a Sequential List</title>
<item><applicabil applicref="a"></applicabil>First item in a sequential
list</item><item>Second item in a sequential list</item><item>Third
item in a sequential list</item><item><applicabil applicref="c"></applicabil>Fourth
item in a sequential list</item><item><applicabil applicref="b"></applicabil>Fifth
item in a sequential list</item></seqlist><randlist>
<title>This is a Random List.</title>
<item><applicabil applicref="a"></applicabil>First Item in a random
