<scope><title> Scope</title>
<para>This manual shall cover the functionality and maintenance of
the MP-3 Hydraulic System.</para>
</scope>
<manstru><title><applicabil applicref="b"></applicabil>Structure Of
Manual</title>
<para>The content of this manual has been arranged by Work Packages
(WP) and Subordinate Work Packages (SWP). The WP and SWP concept is
used to present information in a function/task format. Each WP is
an independent task/process oriented unit, providing only essential
information for operation and maintenance of the test station and
OTB system with minimal referencing.</para>
</manstru>
<coverage><title> Type of Coverage in This Manual</title>
<para>Identifies information which describes the type of coverage
within the manual.</para>
<subpara1><title>Coverage</title><para>Each Work Pack may cover such
subjects as alphabetical index (for a manual), foreword (to a manual),
theory of operation, operating instructions, troubleshooting or fault
isolation, alignment, disassembly, assembly, cleaning, inspection,
and repair. Each WP shall contain the minimum number of pages required
to complete the coverage of the functional task. WPs and SWPs shall
always begin on a right-hand page.</para>
</subpara1>
</coverage>
<indexscheme><title> Scheme Of Indexing</title>
<para>Indexing is provided both numerically and alphabetically. Refer
to for numerical or alphabetical index.</para>
<step1><para>A numerical index of all WP/SWPs contained in this manual
is provided in the manual front matter. The index lists all WP/SWPs
in the manual in alphabetical order by subject, followed by the WP/SWP
number.</para>
</step1>
<step1><para>An alphabetical index of all WP/SWPs contained in this
manual is provided in the manual front matter. The index lists all
WP/SWPs in the manual in alphabetical order by subject, followed by
the WP/SWP number.</para>
</step1>
</indexscheme>
<locinfo applicref="a"><title> Procedure For Locating Specific Information
</title>
<para>This manual uses WPs to present general system information,
preparation for use and shipment, operation, servicing, including
and procedures. The data is broken out from WPs into SWPs as needed
to clarify information. The manual front matter provides a List of
Effective Pages (LOEP) and TOC for the entire manual, while each individual
unit/function specific WP provides a LOEP and TOC referencing the
data contained within the individual WP/SWPs. The data structure of
the manual follows reference designation as close as possible and
information can be found through the use of reference designators.</para>
<subpara1 hci="1"><title>Reference Designators</title><para>WP002
00, provides a general list of nomenclature to reference designators
for Tester Replaceable Units (TRUs)/shop Replaceable Units (SRUs)
which make up the test station.</para>
</subpara1>
</locinfo>
